2025-05-06 13:29:18,083 INFO: Chat message received. Session data: {'_fresh': False, 'company_desc': 'coal mining', 'conversation_history': ['Q: esrs', 'A: <p><strong>ESRS Requirements for Mining, Quarrying, and Coal Sector</strong></p>\n<h3><strong>Environmental Disclosures</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Spills and Incidents</strong><ul>\n<li>Total number of significant spills, volume by substance, and definition of "significant spill" (ESRS E2-28)</li>\n<li>Number of overall significant incidents, including those involving hazardous materials and waste management (ESRS E2-30)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Biodiversity and Ecosystems</strong><ul>\n<li>Average direct land use change in hectares (ESRS E2-67a)</li>\n<li>Percentage of land-use change area rehabilitated/restored, including in protected and key biodiversity areas (ESRS E2-67b)</li>\n<li>Metrics on state of species (ESRS E2-67c)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Health and Safety Disclosures</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Hazards Exposure</strong><ul>\n<li>List of Substances of Very High Concern (SVHCs) for chemical hazards (ESRS S1-29a)</li>\n<li>List of key physical or ergonomic hazards and their inclusion in the health and safety management system (ESRS S1-29b)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Health and Safety Metrics</strong><ul>\n<li>Work-related fatalities, injuries, and recordable ill health, broken down by employees and non-employees (ESRS S1-31)</li>\n<li>Average hours of training per worker on health, safety, and emergency preparedness (ESRS S1-32)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Social Disclosures</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Own Workforce</strong><ul>\n<li>Policies, actions, and targets addressing housing facilities, access to basic services, recreational facilities, and social spaces for workers (ESRS S1-MQC.69a)</li>\n<li>Policies, actions, and targets addressing working time and work-life balance for round-the-clock or remote operations (ESRS S1-MQC.69b)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Work Stoppages</strong><ul>\n<li>Number of work stoppages, including number of employees involved and duration (MQC 7-70)</li>\n<li>Actions taken to resolve major work stoppages (MQC 7-72)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>', 'Q: esrs', 'A: <p><strong>ESRS Requirements for Mining, Quarrying, and Coal Sector</strong></p>\n<h3><strong>Environmental Disclosures</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Spills and Incidents</strong><ul>\n<li>Total number of significant spills, volume by substance, and definition of "significant spill" (ESRS E2-28)</li>\n<li>Number of overall significant incidents, including those involving hazardous materials and waste management (ESRS E2-30)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Biodiversity and Ecosystems</strong><ul>\n<li>Average direct land use change in hectares (ESRS E2-67a)</li>\n<li>Percentage of land-use change area rehabilitated/restored, including in protected and key biodiversity areas (ESRS E2-67b)</li>\n<li>Metrics on state of species (ESRS E2-67c)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Health and Safety Disclosures</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Hazards Exposure</strong><ul>\n<li>List of Substances of Very High Concern (SVHCs) for chemical hazards (ESRS S1-29a)</li>\n<li>List of key physical or ergonomic hazards and their inclusion in the health and safety management system (ESRS S1-29b)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Health and Safety Metrics</strong><ul>\n<li>Work-related fatalities, injuries, and recordable ill health, broken down by employees and non-employees (ESRS S1-31)</li>\n<li>Average hours of training per worker on health, safety, and emergency preparedness (ESRS S1-32)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Social Disclosures</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Own Workforce</strong><ul>\n<li>Policies, actions, and targets addressing housing facilities, access to basic services, recreational facilities, and social spaces for workers (ESRS S1-MQC.69a)</li>\n<li>Policies, actions, and targets addressing working time and work-life balance for round-the-clock or remote operations (ESRS S1-MQC.69b)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Work Stoppages</strong><ul>\n<li>Number of work stoppages, including number of employees involved and duration (MQC 7-70)</li>\n<li>Actions taken to resolve major work stoppages (MQC 7-72)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>', 'Q: explain mining standards', 'A: <p><strong>Mining Standards (ESRS Compliance)</strong></p>\n<h3><strong>Key Aspects of Mining Standards</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Sector Classification</strong>: Defined by NACE codes (listed in Appendix D of the draft ESRS), including mining, quarrying, coal, and related services.</li>\n<li><strong>Materiality Assessment</strong>: Includes two cross-cutting sustainability matters:<ul>\n<li><strong>Incidents and Accidents</strong>: Potential for disastrous environmental, community, worker, and financial impacts (e.g., ground failure, explosions, tailings dam failures).</li>\n<li><strong>Closure of Assets</strong>: Restoration to pre-development ecological functionality or stabilization post-operation to prevent environmental and social impacts.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Disclosure and Application Requirements</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Environmental Disclosures</strong><ul>\n<li>Spills and Incidents (e.g., ESRS E2-28, E2-30)</li>\n<li>Biodiversity and Ecosystems (e.g., ESRS E2-67a, E2-67b, E2-67c)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Health and Safety Disclosures</strong><ul>\n<li>Hazards Exposure (e.g., ESRS S1-29a, S1-29b)</li>\n<li>Health and Safety Metrics (e.g., ESRS S1-31, S1-32)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Social Disclosures</strong><ul>\n<li>Own Workforce (e.g., ESRS S1-MQC.69a, S1-MQC.69b)</li>\n<li>Work Stoppages (e.g., MQC 7-70, MQC 7-72)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Specific Mining Requirements</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Mineral Reserves</strong>:<ul>\n<li>Disclosure of percentage and grade of mineral proven reserves (AR 20)</li>\n<li>Compliance with PERC or CRIRSCO reporting standards (AR 21)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>High-Risk Areas</strong>:<ul>\n<li>Identification of reserves in conflict-affected or high-risk areas (AR 23, AR 24)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Indigenous Communities</strong>:<ul>\n<li>Respect for particular rights, including Free, Prior, and Informed Consent (FPIC)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Application Scope</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Applies to undertakings where mining, quarrying, and coal are significant sectors (as per ESRS 2, AR 13, and draft SEC 1)</li>\n<li>Includes all activities classified under relevant NACE codes, with supplementary activities like crushing and grinding.</li>\n</ul>', 'Q: explain mining standards', 'A: <p><strong>Mining Standards (ESRS Compliance)</strong></p>\n<h3><strong>Key Aspects of Mining Standards</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Sector Classification</strong>: Defined by NACE codes (listed in Appendix D of the draft ESRS), including mining, quarrying, coal, and related services.</li>\n<li><strong>Materiality Assessment</strong>: Includes two cross-cutting sustainability matters:<ul>\n<li><strong>Incidents and Accidents</strong>: Potential for disastrous environmental, community, worker, and financial impacts (e.g., ground failure, explosions, tailings dam failures).</li>\n<li><strong>Closure of Assets</strong>: Restoration to pre-development ecological functionality or stabilization post-operation to prevent environmental and social impacts.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Disclosure and Application Requirements</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Environmental Disclosures</strong><ul>\n<li>Spills and Incidents (e.g., ESRS E2-28, E2-30)</li>\n<li>Biodiversity and Ecosystems (e.g., ESRS E2-67a, E2-67b, E2-67c)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Health and Safety Disclosures</strong><ul>\n<li>Hazards Exposure (e.g., ESRS S1-29a, S1-29b)</li>\n<li>Health and Safety Metrics (e.g., ESRS S1-31, S1-32)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Social Disclosures</strong><ul>\n<li>Own Workforce (e.g., ESRS S1-MQC.69a, S1-MQC.69b)</li>\n<li>Work Stoppages (e.g., MQC 7-70, MQC 7-72)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Specific Mining Requirements</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Mineral Reserves</strong>:<ul>\n<li>Disclosure of percentage and grade of mineral proven reserves (AR 20)</li>\n<li>Compliance with PERC or CRIRSCO reporting standards (AR 21)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>High-Risk Areas</strong>:<ul>\n<li>Identification of reserves in conflict-affected or high-risk areas (AR 23, AR 24)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Indigenous Communities</strong>:<ul>\n<li>Respect for particular rights, including Free, Prior, and Informed Consent (FPIC)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Application Scope</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Applies to undertakings where mining, quarrying, and coal are significant sectors (as per ESRS 2, AR 13, and draft SEC 1)</li>\n<li>Includes all activities classified under relevant NACE codes, with supplementary activities like crushing and grinding.</li>\n</ul>'], 'conversation_id': 16, 'esrs_sector': 'Mining, Quarrying and Coal', 'initialized': True, 'nace_sector': 'B5'} [in C:\Users\Miguel de Juan Urien\Desktop\TFG\ubu-esgenerator\backend\app.py:207]
